In short: I pick the late‑70s/early‑80s AOR classic because it most closely preserves the punchy, guitar‑forward, arena‑ready sound and singalong hooks I seek; the remastered release, despite better packaging and fidelity notes, risks altering the very gloss and attack I value and is therefore less desirable to me.

