In short: Candidate 2’s combination of multitracked stacked harmonies, riff‑focused song lengths, tape‑like punch, preserved headroom and roomy but focused imaging matches my stated priorities far better than Candidate 1’s intimate, acoustic, minimally overdubbed anthology.

